@jvonitter @thenadj This was in the **UIS-6_Keyboard_021.pdf** design spec: https://trello.com/c/VLsCI8iC:

<img width="639" alt="Screen Shot 2019-11-15 at 15 26 42" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/837184/68950553-a8797680-07bc-11ea-97ad-d63b5e5a6e73.png">

Should we revert?

I also saw this behavior on the Oculus Go and Quest headsets and was at the point of logging a bug. 
The app crashes intermittently after resuming from a device sleep. I’ve attached a screen recording of the issue [here](https://drive.google.com/file/d/12Fpjkml2MyIuu3qxgYXQLlhYPeZIz9F4/view?usp=sharing).

@bluemarvin Do you think this is related or a separate issue?

I also saw this behavior on the Oculus Go and Quest headsets and was at the point of logging a bug. 
The app crashes intermittently after resuming from a device sleep. I’ve attached a screen recording of the issue [here](https://drive.google.com/file/d/12Fpjkml2MyIuu3qxgYXQLlhYPeZIz9F4/view?usp=sharing).

@bluemarvin Do you think this is related or a separate issue?

Once an Ad notification has been added to the notification list (even if the device is asleep) the Ad will be confirmed as a View. I believe this is working as expected as when a user on Android then taps this Ad (while the device is awake) in the notification area then this would be confirmed as a Click.

Spec (https://docs.google.com/document/d/1QynlNXswjNfhxGeilooS9TjQsIPkYvgpZH8y9FJdRy4/edit#):

"The Heads up format works in the foreground and the background. The basis for Heads up;
1. Opens in system tray when Ad is in foreground
2. Opens on top of lock screen or non Brave App if running in background"

@mandar-brave @anthonypkeane your thoughts please? If you agree we can just close this ticket as `Wont fix`

